16/09/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The International Court of Justice's (ICJ) deadline for submissions of requests for a hearing on the legality of Kosovo's independence declaration expired on Tuesday (September 15th). 
The legality of the former Serbian province's independence is expected to be defended by the US, Great Britain, France and other supporters starting on December 1st. 
Serbia, Russia, Brazil, Slovakia, and Romania -- among others -- are expected to object to Kosovo's independence, terming it a violation of international law. 
(Zeri, Kosova Sot, Kohavision, RTK - 16/09/09)
